Here's the TUnit lifecycle at each scope:

## 1. Before/After every individual test

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Test)]
    public async Task ResetDatabase(TestContext context)
    {
        await InMemoryDb.ResetAsync();
    }

    [After(Test)]
    public async Task Cleanup(TestContext context)
    {
        // runs after each test
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Order_MustHaveItems() { /* ... */ }
}
```

## 2. Once before/after the class (class-scoped fixture)

```csharp
public class IntegrationTests
{
    private static HttpClient _client = null!;

    [Before(Class)]
    public static async Task StartFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        _client = new HttpClient { BaseAddress = new Uri("http://localhost:5000") };
    }

    [After(Class)]
    public static async Task DisposeFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        _client.Dispose();
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task GetEndpoint_Returns200() { /* ... */ }
}
```

## 3. Once before/after the assembly

```csharp
public static class AssemblyHooks
{
    [Before(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StartWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        // spin up WireMock
    }

    [After(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StopWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        // tear down WireMock
    }
}
```

## 4. Once for the entire test session (global)

```csharp
public static class GlobalSetup
{
    [Before(TestSession)]
    public static async Task ApplyMigrations(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        await Database.MigrateAsync();
    }

    [After(TestSession)]
    public static async Task TearDownDatabase(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        await Database.DropAsync();
    }
}
```

---

**Key points:**

| Scope | Attribute | Method must be |
|-------|-----------|----------------|
| Each test | `[Before(Test)]` / `[After(Test)]` | Instance |
| Class | `[Before(Class)]` / `[After(Class)]` | `static` |
| Assembly | `[Before(Assembly)]` / `[After(Assembly)]` | `static` |
| Session | `[Before(TestSession)]` / `[After(TestSession)]` | `static` |

There's also `[BeforeEvery(Test)]` / `[AfterEvery(Test)]` (and `Class`/`Assembly` variants) for **global cross-cutting hooks** that fire for every test across the run regardless of which class they're in — handy for logging or telemetry.
